CGGO: Capital Group Global Growth Equity ETF

The fund invests primarily in common stocks of companies around the world that the investment adviser believes have the potential for growth. It normally invests at least 80% of its assets in equity securities. Under normal market conditions, the fund will invest significantly in issuers domiciled outside the United States (i.e., at least 40% of its net assets, unless market conditions are not deemed favorable by the fundâ€™s investment adviser, in which case the fund would invest at least 30% of its net assets in issuers domiciled outside the United States). It is non-diversified.
